Professor He Chuan (vice president of Southwest Jiaotong University, which worked on the prototype) told reporters that the train could be \"operational\" within 3-10 years. He added: \"Sichuan has rich rare earth resources, which is very beneficial to our construction of permanent magnet tracks, thus promoting the faster development of experiments.\"<p><div class=\"share_submission\" style=\"position:relative;\">
